Each institution required to register under subsection (b) of this section shall:
Be accredited by an accrediting body recognized and approved by the United States Department of Education;
Submit to the Commission:
Every 2 years, a financial statement reviewed by an independent accountant retained by the institution;
An affidavit from the president or chief executive officer of the institution affirming:
That the institution has not filed for bankruptcy protection under Title 11 of the United States Code during its existence; and
The willingness of the president or the chief executive officer to abide by the provisions of this section;
Proof of good business standing in the state in which the central administration of the institution is incorporated; and
Proof of good academic standing submitted by:
The regulatory higher education entity in the state in which the central administration of the institution is located; or
If the state in which the institution is located does not have a regulatory higher education entity, the accrediting body that accredited the institution;
Promptly notify the Commission of a change in ownership or a change in majority control;
Comply with the Principles of Good Practice for distance education established by the Commission through regulation;
Make public and post on the institution's Web site:
Whether the institution is registered in Maryland; and
The process by which to make complaints against the institution;
Comply with the refund policy and procedures established by the Commission; and
Be subject to complaint investigation by the Office of the Attorney General or the Commission or both.

On or before December 1 each year, the Commission shall report to the Governor and, in accordance with § 2-1246 of the State Government Article, the General Assembly:
The number of institutions of postsecondary education that apply for registration under this section;
The type and size of the institutions that apply;
The number of institutions approved for registration;
The number of institutions denied registration; and
The number of Maryland students enrolled in institutions required to register under this section.
